        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-31T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="1070" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1070">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/7–3145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1070<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-31T20:00:00+02:00">July 31, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4640. Re this Embassy’s memo July 21<note n="1" xml:id="d1070fn1">To the French
                        Ministry of Foreign Affairs. Not printed. Cf. <ref target="#d1062">documents
                            Nos. 1062</ref> and <ref target="#d1065">1065</ref>.</note> pertaining
                    to control by Allies to be exercised in Greece during forthcoming elections,
                    memo has been received from Foreign Office dated July 20 [<hi rend="italic">30</hi>].<note n="2" xml:id="d1070fn2">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Confirming my 4395 July 21<note n="3" xml:id="d1070fn3">
                        <ref target="#d1065">Document No. 1065</ref>.</note> this memo informs
                    Embassy that French Government accepts readily to participate in Four Power
                    control of these elections.</p>
                <p>French Foreign Office furthermore shares views of American Government re
                    necessity of keeping these consultations secret until answers of four interested
                    Governments are received and Greek Government informed officially.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
